library(tidyverse)

prices = read_csv("/Users/alexanderkell/Documents/SGI/Projects/11-starter-kits/data/processed/scenarios/Kenya/net_zero/Results/MCAPrices.csv")

── Column specification ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
cols(
  timeslice = col_character(),
  commodity = col_character(),
  region = col_character(),
  prices = col_double(),
  year = col_double()
)
prices
prices_grouped = prices %>% group_by(commodity, year) %>% summarise(price = mean(prices))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'commodity'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
prices_grouped
prices_grouped %>% ggplot() + geom_line(aes(x=year, y=price, color=commodity)) + theme_bw()



capacity = read_csv("/Users/alexanderkell/Documents/SGI/Projects/11-starter-kits/data/processed/scenarios/Kenya/net_zero/Results/MCACapacity.csv")

── Column specification ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
cols(
  technology = col_character(),
  dst_region = col_character(),
  region = col_character(),
  agent = col_character(),
  sector = col_character(),
  type = col_character(),
  year = col_double(),
  capacity = col_double()
)
head(capacity)
capacity_summed = capacity %>% group_by(technology, sector, year, agent) %>% summarise(capacity=sum(capacity))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'technology', 'sector', 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
head(capacity_summed)
ggplot(data=filter(capacity_summed, sector=="power"), aes(x=year, y=capacity, color=technology, linetype=agent)) + geom_line() + theme_classic()

ggplot(data=filter(capacity_summed, sector=="power"), aes(x=year, y=capacity, fill=technology)) + geom_bar(stat='identity', colour="black") + facet_grid(cols=vars(agent)) + theme_classic()

lcoe = read_csv("/Users/alexanderkell/Documents/SGI/Projects/11-starter-kits/data/processed/scenarios/Kenya/net_zero/Results/MCAMetric_Lcoe.csv")
Missing column names filled in: 'X1' [1]
── Column specification ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
cols(
  X1 = col_double(),
  timeslice = col_character(),
  region = col_character(),
  installed = col_double(),
  technology = col_character(),
  year = col_double(),
  agent = col_character(),
  category = col_character(),
  sector = col_character(),
  LCOE = col_double()
)
lcoe = lcoe %>% filter_if(~is.numeric(.), all_vars(!is.infinite(.)))
head(lcoe)
lcoe_summed = lcoe %>% group_by(technology, sector, year, agent) %>% summarise(lcoe=mean(LCOE))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'technology', 'sector', 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
head(lcoe_summed)
ggplot(data=filter(lcoe_summed, sector=="power"), aes(x=year, y=lcoe, color=technology)) + geom_line() + theme_classic()
ggsave("/Users/alexanderkell/Documents/SGI/Projects/11-starter-kits/reports/figures/net_zero-lcoe_line_graph.pdf")
